(c) 	strictly enforce and intensify compliance with the Municipal Ordinances particularly on no littering policy among the residents;
(d) 	recommend to the Sangguniang Bayan (SB) policies and possible measures that will ensure full compliance by the barangays on the provisions of RA No. 9003 and;
(e) 	consider imposing fines and penalties for violators of the Anti-Littering policy as well as filing of administrative cases against erring government officials as provided by Sections 49 and 50 of RA No. 9003.

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive, through the Bids and Awards Committee, 

(a) consider the general policy of the government in acquiring brand new equipment after appropriate consideration of availability of funds; 

(b) fully consider the general obsolescence of the transport and heavy equipment, the availability of spare parts, and the quality, degree and extent of repair and maintenance requirements in the acquisition of second-hand/reconditioned equipment; 

(c) conduct technical study before entering into purchase agreement of second-hand vehicle and; 

(d) strictly adhere to DBM NBC 446-A in the procurement of the second-hand motor vehicles.

